The Dominican Republic’s borders are closed and international flights have been suspended. Although limited commercial options are still departing via the US, British Nationals have not been able to book onto these flights.
If you cannot leave the Dominican Republic at this time, see advice on staying in Dominican Republic during coronavirus.
UK special flights
There are currently no further special flights organised from the Dominican Republic.
This travel advice will be updated with further information on any future special flights and other options to leave the Dominican Republic as soon as this is available. Sign up for travel advice email alerts and follow the British Embassy on Facebook and Twitter.
Future options
The British Embassy is in contact with airlines, the Dominican authorities and other governments to make sure commercial options for returning to the UK are available as soon as possible.
This travel advice will be updated when departure options become available. Sign up for travel advice email alerts and follow the British Embassy on Facebook and Twitter.
You will need to pay for your return travel to the UK. If departure options are available but you cannot afford the travel costs and have exhausted all other options for getting funds, you may be eligible to apply for an emergency loan from the government. This is a last resort option and you would need to repay the loan when you are back in the UK. For more information, you should contact Corporate Travel Management (CTM). CTM are a commercial partner of the FCO and are authorised to administer such loans on behalf of the FCO.
Your journey home
The National Travel Health Network and Centre (NaTHNaC) provides advice on how to stay safe as you travel by air.
If you’re returning home before 8 June, follow the guidance for when you return to the UK on steps you should take to protect yourself and others. From 8 June there will be new rules for entering the UK.
Help and support
If you need urgent consular assistance, you can contact the British Embassy on + 1 809 472 7111. Select option 1 for English, then option 2 for consular emergencies.
The Embassy cannot provide further information or advice about departure options over the phone.
Sign up for travel advice email alerts and follow the British Embassy on Twitter and Facebook.
